Evaluation samples

Source: R/samples.R
nes_samples.Rd

nes_samples is a data frame of 85 NES evaluation samples, each with a contiguous target change.

samples_view() opens an HTML viewer displaying samples' input excerpts and target outputs with diff highlighting, along with edit history and variables. Use the Prev/Next buttons (or left/right arrow keys) to navigate between samples.

Usage

nes_samples

samples_view(x = nes_samples, n = 1L)

Format

A data frame with 85 rows and 4 columns:

id

Character. Sample identifier derived from the source filename.

input

List-column. Each element is a list with components edit_history, excerpt, and variables.

output

Character. The target editable region content.

tags

List-column of character vectors.

Arguments

x

The nes_samples data frame.

n

Initial row index to display.

Value

x, invisibly.
